\v 11 So Simon Peter got into \add the boat\add*\ef + \fr 21:11 \ft ﻿*Here the direct object is supplied from context in the English translation \ef* and hauled the net to the land, full of large fish—one hundred fifty-three—and \add although there\add*\ef + \fr 21:11 \ft ﻿*Here “\add although\add*” is supplied as a component of the participle (“were”) which is understood as concessive \ef* were so many, the net was not torn. 
