\s1 Peter and the Other Disciple Jesus Loved
\m 
\v 20 Peter turned \add and\add*\ef + \fr 21:20 \ft ﻿*Here “\add and\add*” is supplied because the previous participle (“turned”) has been translated as a finite verb \ef* saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following \add them\add*\ef + \fr 21:20 \ft ﻿*Here the direct object is supplied from context in the English translation \ef* (who also leaned back on his chest at the dinner and said, “Lord, who is the one betraying you?”) 
